{{Quote|Those sleep-imprinting sessions on the journey here seem to have ''worked...!'' I've enough information about Metalorn to keep ''one step'' ahead of pursuit.|Leia Organa|<ref name="MSW30">[[Star Wars (1977) 30|''Star Wars'' (1977) 30]]</ref>}}
'''Hypno-imprinting''', also called '''hypno-indoctrination'''<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> and '''sleep-imprinting''',<ref name="MSW30" />  was the use of hypnosis to implant orders, post-hypnotic commands,<ref name="EGWT" /> or to impart tactical information en route to a mission.<ref name="MSW30" />

Hypno-imprinting was also used to [[Brainwashing|brainwash]] [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance]] [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoners]] while they were incarcerated by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. The prisoners were then released and the hypno-imprinting forced the prisoners to spy on the Alliance without the Rebels knowing what they were doing.<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref>

